resources.string:
In Spreadsheet Scoring touch the:<br/>
    <br/>&#x25C9;&#x00A0;Plot Icon to expand/collapse Specimens;
    <br/>&#x25C9;&#x00A0;Touch the Trait Instances to display if the Trait Instance belongs to a Specimen/Sub-Plot or Plot;
    <br/>&#x25C9;&#x00A0;Touch the Individual/Specimen icons to display the Plot Attributes;
    <br/>&#x25C9;&#x00A0;Touch any <b>-</b> cell to score a Trait.<br/><br/>
    A Plot or Specimen can:
     <br/>&#x25C9;&#x00A0;Be Deactivated; or
     <br/>&#x25C9;&#x00A0;Have Tags and photos attached by a Long Press on the Plot or Specimen info columns to display the menu.
<br/>
<p>
Action bar and Menu options available are:
<br/><b>Find Plots</b> - Locate plots using various criteria (Tip: Swipe left/right in Find screen);
<br/><b>Zoom In/Out</b> - Several zoom levels cater for slightly more or less information;
<br/><b>Field View</b> - Displays the Field View screen;
<br/><b>Text Size</b> - For adjusting the text size of the sample values;
<br/><b>Location</b> - Enable/Disable location services;
<br/><b>Configure</b> - Configure the information to display in the Plot Attributes;
<br/><b>Elapsed Days As Count</b> - Checkbox to change the display of Elapsed Days from a Date to Number of Days since the Trial planting date;
<br/><b>Offer N days for DATE</b> - Checkbox to change Date from calendar input to single selection of days since \'today\';

<br/><b>Unlock Scored Traits</b> - Unlocks any scored Traits to allow modification without additional warnings;
<br/><b>Change Screen Orientation</b> - Change screen orientation, e.g. change from Landscape to Portrait. A 3 second delay allows the tablet to be turned to the desired orientation before it locks again;
<br/> <b>Choose Plot Colours</b> - Three colours are available for Plots and Traits and more can be added by our development team on request;
<br/> <b>Show/Hide Specimens</b> - Closes or Shows all the specimens if scoring only Plots and not scoring Specimens/Sub Plots.
<br/> <b>Fixed Plot info</b> - Enables selection for column display of inactive Traits and Plot Attributes.
<br/>


</p>
